ce:section.ce:para:
As a visible responsive semiconductor material, the CQDs/BC UV–vis DRS spectra peak was red-shifted from the initial 250 nm (CQDs) to 310 nm (Fig. 1(e)), and the absorption range and intensity of CQDs/BC in the visible region were significantly wider and stronger, indicating that CQDs/BC had a stronger visible light absorption capability and higher light utilization than CQDs (Guo et al., 2024; Wang et al., 2024). The direct optical bandgap (Eg
                        ) of CQDs and CQDs/BCs was estimated by fitting the DRS spectra based on Tauc curves (Fig. 1(e)), the Eg
                         of CQDs/BC (0.75 eV) is smaller than that of CQDs (0.81 eV).
